featured.text: The 60 pilot whales swam ashore as a result of (A) a large winter storm off the coast of Cape Cod. (B) a behavior currently unknown to scientists.
For those who speak into the wind phone, 30 is always there: They believe that their messages will— through some unknown way—reach the deceased.

definition.zh_def: 未知的；不明的；不熟悉的事物或人。
definition.en_def: Not known or familiar; something or someone that is not recognized.
definition.example: The origins of the ancient artifact remain unknown.
